- **WCAG compliance preparation** – structure responses for Web Content Accessibility Guidelines.
- **Screen reader compatibility** – ensure JSON responses work well with assistive technologies.
- **Keyboard navigation support** – design API interactions that support keyboard-only navigation.
- **High contrast data presentation** – provide accessible data formatting options.
- **Multilingual accessibility** – ensure accessibility features work across different languages.
- **Cognitive load reduction** – simplify API responses to reduce cognitive burden on users.
- **Alternative format support** – prepare for audio, braille, and other alternative data formats.
